# Use the frontend-design skill first

Before editing or creating ANY frontend code (components, pages, styles,
animations) in this project, FIRST read and follow the skill at
`.cursor/skills/frontend-design/SKILL.md`.

Apply its guidance on every change:

- Commit to a clear, bold aesthetic direction before writing code.
- Distinctive typography (no generic system/Inter/Roboto/Arial fonts).
- Cohesive color system via CSS variables; dominant colors with sharp accents.
- High-impact, well-orchestrated motion (use `framer-motion`, already installed).
- Intentional spatial composition; atmosphere and texture over flat solid colors.
- Avoid generic "AI-generated" looks, cliché gradients, and predictable layouts.

This project's established aesthetic is a warm, vintage, analog/editorial
illustrated portfolio (cream paper, near-black ink, `Fraunces` serif display,
hand-drawn dogs). Keep new work cohesive with that point of view.
